Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @chicken thigh{210%g}(diced) and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Fry, turning frequently, until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
packaging.

While the chicken cooks, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic
press{}).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%tin} in a #sieve{}, then put half of them
into a #bowl{} and roughly mash with a #fork{}. Add the remaining whole beans to
the bowl.

Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in the sieve.

Once the chicken is browned, add the @shallot{} and @chorizo{60%g} to the pan.

Fry, stirring frequently, until the shallot has softened and the chorizo has
started to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @Mexican style spice mix{2}, sweetcorn and half the garlic. Cook,
stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

TIP: Add less spice if you don't like heat.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1%tin}, @water{200%ml}, @chicken stock paste{15%g}
and black beans (whole and mashed).

Season the sauce with salt, pepper and @sugar{1/4%tsp}. Bring to the boil,
stirring continuously, then reduce the heat to medium.

Simmer until the mixture has thickened and the chicken is cooked, ~{6-8%minutes}.
Stir every 2 mins or so.

IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the stew simmers, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Halve the @ciabatta{2} and lay onto a #baking tray{}, cut-side up.

Spread over the remaining garlic and drizzle with the @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}. 
Season with salt and pepper.

Bake the garlic bread on the top shelf of your oven until golden,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the stew is cooked, stir in the @baby spinach{40%g} a handful at a time
until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{} if needed.

Remove the stew from the heat, then taste and add salt and pepper if you feel
it needs it.

Serve in #bowls{} with the cheese scattered on top and the garlic ciabatta
alongside. Enjoy!